liant on fossil fuels’ and ‘100 per cent renewable energy’. This LT-LEDS aligns with this aim as well as with the aims of Tonga’s Second NDC which states a target of reducing GHG emissions from the combustion of fossil fuels by 13 percent (16 Gg) by 2030, compared to 2006.","page":39},{"doc_id":26791,"document":"LTS","version":"LTS 1.0","doc_type":"LTS","status":"Active","area":"Transport sector mitigation target","scope":"Subsector targets","ghg":"Non GHG","type":"Vehicle efficiency targets","conditionality":"Unconditional","year":"no date provided","content":"The NDC specifies a Transport sector measure of 2 percent efficiency gain per year for newly purchased light duty vehicles to contribute to the NDC emission reduction target. The LT-LEDS pathway for transport supports this NDC aim","page":39},{"doc_id":26791,"document":"LTS","version":"LTS 1.0","doc_type":"LTS","status":"Active","area":"Transport sector mitigation target","scope":"Subsector targets","ghg":"Non GHG","type":"Zero emission vehicle targets","conditionality":"Unconditional","year":"2030 to 2050","content":"Public adoption of 50 percent electric vehicles (EVs).","page":48},{"doc_id":80496,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","area":"Overall mitigation target","scope":"Overall mitigation target","ghg":"GHG","type":"GHG: Base year","conditionality":"Conditional","year":2035,"content":"Tonga wishes to communicate the following targets for the third NDC:\nEnergy: 70 Gg CO2e reduction in GHG emissions by 2035 (25 Gg CO2e from the electricity sector and 45 Gg CO2e from the transport sector).\nIPPU: Recommitment to identifying a GHG emission baseline through a centralized database, and the non-emission target of a 30% reduction in HFC imports.\nAFOLU: Recommitment to identifying a GHG emission target through a forest inventory, and the non-emission targets of scaling land-based carbon sinks with the planting of one million trees and further shifts towards sustainable agriculture and livestock practices.\nWaste: Recommitment to identifying a GHG emission target through a waste MRV system, database and infrastructure upgrade, and the non-emission target of reducing the generation and consumption of single-use plastics by 2030.","page":16},{"doc_id":80496,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","area":"Energy sector target","scope":"Sector-wide","ghg":"Non GHG","type":"Other non-GHG energy targets","conditionality":"Conditional","year":2030,"content":"These priorities align with Tonga’s goal of increasing the share of renewable electricity (targeting 70% by 2030), a goal that will require considerable expansion of solar, wind, and battery capacity, making technology transfer and capacity support essential.","page":33},{"doc_id":80496,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","area":"Transport sector mitigation target","scope":"Sector-wide","ghg":"GHG","type":"GHG: Base year","conditionality":"Conditional","year":2035,"content":"Reduce transport emissions in the energy sector by 26 GgCO2e by 2030 and 45 GgCO2e by 2035 compared to the baseline emissions of 2006.","page":40}],"measures":[{"doc_id":17761,"document":"First Generation NDC","version":"NDC 1.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Alternative fuels","purpose":"Promote alternative fuels","instrument":"Biofuels support measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"Interested in developing biofuels for both transport and electricity generation","page":null,"modes":[],"geography":[],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":17762,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Mode shift and demand management","purpose":"Economic conditions for sustainable transport","instrument":"Vehicle taxation","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"incentives for purchasing more efficient vehicles through (...) import tariffs","page":6,"modes"